{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17532654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17532654"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:28:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:28:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14697"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14697","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14697"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.18,0.42,0.01,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7390"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111788"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7390","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7390"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14697"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93858"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"81"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"1453"},{"type":"tags","id":"2342"},{"type":"tags","id":"3546"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18029"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45753"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111788","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111788"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a health assessment. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She works as an accountant and leads a sedentary lifestyle. On examination, she appears well with a waist circumference of 92 cm. Her pulse rate is 76/min, blood pressure 142/88 mmHg. Blood tests reveal: fasting glucose 6.2 mmol/L (3.9-5.5) and high-density lipoprotein 0.9 mmol/L (\u0026gt;1.0).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following additional features if present would be consistent with a diagnosis of metabolic syndrome?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Total cholesterol 6.8 mmol/L (\u003C5.4)","Body mass index 32 kg/m2","Triglycerides 2.9 mmol/L (\u003C1.7)","Left ventricular ejection fraction \u003C50%","Low-density lipoprotein 4.9 mmol/L (\u003C3.0)"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient already demonstrates four features of metabolic syndrome: increased waist circumference, elevated blood pressure, elevated fasting glucose, and reduced HDL concentration. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElevated \u003Cstrong\u003Etriglycerides\u003C/strong\u003E \u0026gt;1.7 mmol/L is another diagnostic criterion for metabolic syndrome, though not needed in this case for diagnosis as at least three criteria are already met. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn elevated \u003Cstrong\u003Ebody mass index\u003C/strong\u003E is not a criterion for metabolic syndrome, which uses waist circumference to define central obesity rather than BMI.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElevated \u003Cstrong\u003Etotal cholesterol\u003C/strong\u003E is not a criterion for metabolic syndrome, though it may coexist and contribute to cardiovascular risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced \u003Cstrong\u003Eleft ventricular ejection fraction\u003C/strong\u003E is not a criterion for metabolic syndrome, though cardiovascular disease may be a consequence of metabolic syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElevated \u003Cstrong\u003Elow-density lipoprotein\u003C/strong\u003E is not a criterion for metabolic syndrome, though it often coexists and contributes to cardiovascular risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMetabolic syndrome represents a cluster of risk factors that significantly increase the risk of cardiovascular disease and type 2 diabetes. Management focuses on lifestyle modifications including diet, exercise, and weight reduction, along with specific treatment of individual components such as hypertension and dyslipidaemia.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Metabolic syndrome requires three or more of: increased waist circumference, elevated triglycerides, reduced HDL, elevated blood pressure, and elevated fasting glucose.","Although each of the components of metabolic syndrome is a risk factor for cardiovascular disease, when a person has three or more risk factors, the chance of developing a serious cardiovascular condition increases."],"references":["About Metabolic Syndrome. In: American Heart Association [Online]. Available from: https://www.heart.org/en/health-topics/metabolic-syndrome/about-metabolic-syndrome","Harris M. F. (2013). The metabolic syndrome. Australian family physician, 42(8), 524\u2013527.. Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/afp/2013/august/the-metabolic-syndrome"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93858"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14697"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93858","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93858"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-19T21:28:20+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-19T21:28:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7390"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111788"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":